      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:3:45:9",
      "text": [
        " مَمْلُوكٍ قَذَفَ مُحْصَنَةً حُرَّةً قَالَ يُجْلَدُ ثَمَانِينَ لِأَنَّهُ إِنَّمَا يُجْلَدُ لِحَقِّهَا ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad, from Ali Bin Al Hakam, from Musa Bin Bakr, from Zurara, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Ja’far<sup>asws</sup> regarding an owned (slave) who slandered a married free woman. He<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘He would be whipped eighty (lashes) because, but rather he is being whipped for her rights’."
        ]
      }
